This paper is about the implementation and deployment of a Data Management System in the context of the EU DataGrid project. The paper discusses the components of the system, their interaction, and the experience and feedback received from users. The paper also discusses the lessons learned and the motivation for the architecture of the next generation of Data Management Services. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.DB (Databases), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
